  "prompt": "What are some good movies about a person that has a hidden power that he/she couldn't use until put into a pressure situation?",
  "response": "There are a number of compelling movies with protagonists who uncover hidden powers under pressure. Here are some noteworthy ones:\n\n1. **\"Unbreakable\" (2000)** - Directed by M. Night Shyamalan, this film stars Bruce Willis as a man who realizes he has superhuman abilities after surviving a catastrophic train accident. Samuel L. Jackson co-stars as a comic book enthusiast who helps him embrace his hidden power.\n\n2. **\"The Matrix\" (1999)** - In this iconic sci-fi movie directed by the Wachowskis, Keanu Reeves plays Neo, a hacker who discovers he has extraordinary abilities when he is drawn into a revolutionary fight against a dystopian system.\n\n3. **\"Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone\" (2001)** - Based on J.K. Rowling's novel, this film follows a young boy named Harry Potter who discovers he is a wizard and has magical powers when he enters Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.\n\n4. **\"Spider-Man\" (2002)** - Directed by Sam Raimi, this movie features Tobey Maguire as Peter Parker, who gains superhuman abilities after being bitten by a genetically altered spider. He must learn to use his powers responsibly when faced with adversity.\n\n5. **\"Push\" (2009)** - A sci-fi thriller directed by Paul McGuigan, featuring Chris Evans as a man with telekinetic abilities who is hunted by a government agency while trying to uncover the mystery of his powers and escape their grasp.\n\n6. **\"Chronicle\" (2012)** - Directed by Josh Trank, this found-footage film tells the story of three teenagers who develop powerful telekinetic abilities and face intense situations that force them to confront their hidden strengths and weaknesses.\n\n7. **\"Carrie\" (1976)** - Directed by Brian De Palma, this adaptation of Stephen King's novel centers on a shy high school girl named Carrie (played by Sissy Spacek) who discovers her telekinetic powers under the oppressive pressure of her abusive mother and cruel classmates.\n\n8. **\"Shazam!\" (2019)** - Directed by David F. Sandberg, this film follows a teenage boy named Billy Batson who discovers he can transform into an adult superhero with extraordinary powers by uttering the word \"Shazam.\"\n\nThese films showcase protagonists who uncover and harness their hidden powers when faced with dire circumstances, often leading to profound personal growth and epic confrontations.",
